- OS Version: Windows_NT ia32 10.0.10586

It seems to break on the <T,T> parts

Steps to Reproduce:
1. Create a tsx file with at least one class that extends React.Component 
2. See!

``` tsx
import * as React from 'react';

class Test extends React.Component<{},{}> {
    public constructor() {
        super();
        console.log('created');
    }
}

class OtherTest extends React.Component<{},{}> {
    public constructor(){
        super();
        console.log('created');
    }
}
```

